With Sho Madjozi’s carefree black girl outlook, a New Age athleisure take on tinguvu, and her biracial luminescence, it has been argued, that the idea of a Xitsonga-speaking artist has become more palatable. READ MORE: Sho Madjozi’s musical lineage is larger than large Growing up around the globe as a result of her father’s work, she collected an array of influences from South Africa, Tanzania, Senegal and the United States. Although she is yet to deny the privilege that this has afforded her, Madjozi continues to ride the Limpopo wave. To many, her choice to claim the identity of a village girl is unsettling.